[{"id":"VR876942","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Which of the following provides a correct ratio <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the ratio of U sub A to U sub B, to U sub C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"the ratio of U sub A to U sub B, to U sub C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>A</mtext></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>B</mtext></msub><mo>:</mo><msub><mi>U</mi><mtext>C</mtext></msub></math></span></span> for the electric potential energies of arrangements <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>, <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"> <mtext>B</mtext> </math></span></span>, and <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"C\" role=\"math\"><math alttext=\"C\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mtext>C</mtext></math></span></span>, respectively?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR876942_rubric","features":[{"type":"sharedpassage","html":"<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three isolated arrangements of charged spheres are shown. The charges of the spheres and the distances between the spheres are indicated. Assume the electric potential energy is zero when the spheres are an infinite distance apart, and that the radii of the spheres are small compared to the distance between them.</p>\n\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows pairs of charged spheres in three arrangements labeled Arrangement A, Arrangement B, and Arrangement C. Arrangement A shows a sphere of charge positive Q at a distance R to the left of a sphere of charge negative Q. Arrangement B shows a sphere of charge positive Q at a distance R to the left of a sphere of charge positive Q. Arrangement C shows a sphere of charge positive Q at a distance 2 R to the left of a sphere of charge positive Q. A note states that the figure is not drawn to scale.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR876942.g04.svg\" /></div>\n"}],"choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the ratio of negative 2 to 2, to 1\"><math alttext=\"the ratio of negative 2 to 2, to 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>−</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the ratio of 2 to 2, to 1\"><math alttext=\"the ratio of 2 to 2, to 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the ratio of negative 4 to 4, to 1\"><math alttext=\"the ratio of negative 4 to 4, to 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mo>−</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the ratio of 4 to 4, to 1\"><math alttext=\"the ratio of 4 to 4, to 1\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>:</mo><mn>1</mn></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":0}]